    "narrative": "For today's matchup, **Corbin Carroll** leads the squad with an elite 81.24 efficiency score. Despite the tough draw against Scherzer, **Corbin Carroll** benefits from a prime two-hole spot and his unique ability to generate value even when his base projection is pressured, making him our anchor. **Tyler Soderstrom** (76.91) and **James Wood** (73.32) provide massive upside against Fedde and Houser, respectively. **Tyler Soderstrom** exploits a significant SP skill gap and a favorable park, while **James Wood** leverages a leadoff assignment and a neutral platoon advantage to climb into the high-70s. These three serve as the core of our effort to gain ground in the scarcest category, stolen bases.\n\nOur most critical lineup decisions centered on maximizing SB-positive environments against pitchers with slower deliveries. **Brice Turang** (66.08) and **Dalton Rushing** (64.84) both received notable boosts from the \"Slow SP Delivery\" metric, allowing them to remain high-priority starts despite mid-tier matchups. **Jose Caballero** (63.87) also finds his way into the lineup; his dynamic platoon edge against Cameron\u2014offsetting the \"Wind In\" penalty\u2014highlights our focus on high-efficiency, high-speed profiles. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (69.30) remains a set-and-forget play, as his plate discipline and platoon advantage against Warren keep him well above the 60-point threshold for strong starts.\n\nThe most difficult exclusion today was **Seiya Suzuki** (51.44), who fell just outside the cutoff. While **Seiya Suzuki** provides solid production, the optimizer prioritized **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Mickey Moniak** due to superior park and platoon contexts. **Seiya Suzuki** ultimately suffered from a poor BvP history (37 PA) and a lack of elite efficiency relative to our starting outfielders. We are closely monitoring the weather at the games impacted by the \"Wind In\" warning, specifically noting that **Jazz Chisholm Jr.**, **Jose Caballero**, and **Giancarlo Stanton** carry increased risk if that wind persists during their high-leverage plate appearances. All other rostered assets, including **Alex Freeland**, **Max Muncy**, and our bench depth of **Josh Naylor**, **Austin Riley**, **Trevor Story**, **Gabriel Moreno**, **Luis Campusano**, **Zach McKinstry**, **Kyle Karros**, **Carson Williams**, and **Travis Bazzana**, remain on high alert for pinch-hit opportunities should the game states shift.",
